The paper discusses experimental evaluation of a reconfigurable antenna system for achieving blind interference alignment in a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel. This involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and architecture (cs.AR). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
